        <div>
            As physical and mental health are often closely linked we have gathered some resources to point people who are looking for help in the right direction.
        </div>
        <br>
        <div>
            <a href="https://www.nhs.uk/oneyou/every-mind-matters/" target=”_blank”>NHS Every Mind Matters</a><br>
            This website provides information and advice on mental health, including self-care tips and resources to help manage stress, anxiety, and depression.
            <br><br>
            <a href="https://www.mind.org.uk/" target=”_blank”>Mind</a><br>
            Mind is a UK-based charity that provides advice and support to those experiencing mental health problems. They offer a range of services, including a helpline, online support groups, and local support services.
            <br><br>
            <a href="https://www.samaritans.org/" target=”_blank”>Samaritans</a><br>
            Samaritans is a UK-based charity that provides confidential emotional support 24 hours a day, 7 days a week. You can contact them by phone, email, or in person at one of their branches.
            <br><br>
            <a href="https://youngminds.org.uk/" target=”_blank”>Young Minds</a><br>
            Young Minds is a UK-based charity that focuses on mental health support for children and young people. They provide information and advice for young people, parents, and professionals, as well as a helpline for those in need of immediate support.
            <br><br>
            <a href="https://www.rethink.org/" target=”_blank”>Rethink Mental Illness</a><br>
            Rethink Mental Illness is a UK-based charity that provides information and support for those affected by mental illness, including their families and carers. They offer a range of services, including a helpline and online support groups.
            <br><br>
            <a href="https://www.mentalhealth.org.uk/" target=”_blank”>The Mental Health Foundation</a><br>
            The Mental Health Foundation is a UK-based charity that works to prevent mental health problems and improve mental health for all. They provide information and advice on mental health, as well as campaigns and research.
            <br><br>
            <a href="https://www.thecalmzone.net/" target=”_blank”>Calm</a><br>
            Calm is a UK-based charity that focuses on preventing male suicide. They provide support and resources for men experiencing mental health problems, including a helpline and online chat service.
            <br><br>
            <a href="https://papyrus-uk.org/" target=”_blank”>Papyrus</a><br>
            Papyrus is a UK-based charity that focuses on preventing suicide in young people. They provide support and resources for young people and their families, including a helpline and online chat service.
            <br><br>
            Remember that seeking help for mental health problems is a sign of strength, not weakness. If you or someone you know is struggling with mental health issues, please reach out to one of these resources or speak to a healthcare professional.
